OL,3,CWelsh and UK Government row over
OL,4,Cplanned deposit return scheme
OL,6,FIn his statement, the UK Environment
OL,7,FMinister wrote that "As it stands,
OL,8,Fwhen our DRS launches, businesses and
OL,9,Fconsumers will be protected by the
OL,10,Fmarket access principles of the UKIM
OL,11,FAct for the sale of drinks in glass
OL,12,Fbottles across the UK. In plain terms,
OL,13,Fthis means that drinks in glass
OL,14,Fcontainers made or imported into
OL,15,FEngland, Scotland and Northern Ireland
OL,16,Fwill not be subject to a Welsh DRS
OL,17,Fwhich includes glass."
